 and prawns then chop <b>Turbo\/0.5 sec\/3-4 times<b>."},{"content":"Add egg yolk, soy sauce, sesame oil and rice wine vinegar then mix <b>1 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Grease Varoma dish and tray with peanut oil then set aside."},{"content":"Place 1 wonton wrapper onto a clean work surface. Place 1 heaped tsp of mince mixture in the middle of wonton wrapper."},{"content":"Brush all edges of the wrapper with a little egg white, then fold wonton wrapper in half diagonally to enclose filling, forming a triangle shape."},{"content":"Using your fingertips, seal all edges to eliminate any air pockets. Gently pull 2 remaining corners together (over enclosed filling) and press together to seal."},{"content":"Repeat with remaining filling and wrappers to make approx. 20 wontons (you may have leftover wrappers). Place all wontons into Varoma dish and onto Varoma tray, then set aside."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Broth"},{"content":"Place garlic, ginger and spring onions in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add oil and sauté <b>2 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add water, stock paste, fish sauce and sesame oil then cook <b>15 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Place Varoma with wontons into position and cook <b>12 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set Varoma aside."},{"content":"Add pak choi, shiitake mushrooms and bamboo shoots then cook <b>2 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Divide wontons between serving bowls, then ladle broth over wontons and garnish with extra sliced chilli before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>  for the chicken stock paste recipe."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h","4 portions"]}